The US Geological Survey measured today's quake, which was centred in the northeast of the island, at magnitude 6.3 and a depth of 7 kilometres. JOHANNESBURG â€“ A strong earthquake has jolted the Indonesian island of Lombok as it tries to recover from a quake earlier this month that killed 460 people. The US Geological Survey measured today's quake, which was centred in the northeast of the island, at magnitude 6.3 and a depth of 7 kilometres. There are no immediate reports of damage or injuries. A magnitude 7.0 quake earlier this month damaged tens of thousands of homes and displaced several hundred thousand people on Lombok.